ning during urination. If a serious infection, an opportunistic infection, or sepsis develops, tofacitinib should be interrupted until the infection is controlled.', 'Others', 'Valrubicin', 'Antithymocyte immunoglobulin (rabbit), Secukinumab, Anifrolumab, Ravulizumab, Mycophenolic acid, Methotrexate, Tacrolimus, Abatacept, Apremilast, Inebilizumab, Belumosudil, More', 'Major', NULL, 'DDInter', 'pharmacodynamic', NULL, 'https://ddinter2.scbdd.com/server/interact/121919/', '[1] "Product Information. Xeljanz (tofacitinib)." Pfizer U.S. Pharmaceuticals Group, New York, NY.', 1767369485);
